		"body": "When setting or resetting the master password, if the user enters two different passwords in the \"Enter password\" and \"Re-enter password\" fields, the Save button is silently disabled without any feedback message explaining why.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds a red error message — \"Passwords do not match!\" — below the \"Re-enter password\" field when the two values differ. The message only appears when both fields have content and don't match.\r\n\r\n**Changes:**\r\n- File: [packages/app-desktop/gui/MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx](cci:7://file:///d:/GSoC%202026/joplin/packages/app-desktop/gui/MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx:0:0-0:0)\r\n- Used `var(--joplin-color-error)` for consistent error styling\r\n- Message wrapped in [_()](cci:1://file:///d:/GSoC%202026/joplin/packages/app-desktop/gui/NotePropertiesDialog.tsx:233:1-236:2) for translation support\r\n\r\n**Testing:**\r\n1. Type same password in both fields → No error, Save enabled\r\n2. Type different passwords → Red error appears, Save disabled\r\n3. Fix second field to match → Error disappears, Save enabled\r\n4. Leave second field empty → No error shown\r\n5. Test in Reset mode → Error works there too\r\n",
